      "number": 1,
      "title": "「是...的」结构 — The Structure shì...de",
      "explanation": "The 是(shì)...的(de) structure is used to emphasise information about a past event — specifically the time, place, manner, or agent. The action has already happened; 是(shì)...的(de) focuses on the circumstances. Structure: Subject + 是(shì) + [emphasis: time/place/manner] + Verb + 的(de). The object can go before or after 的(de).",
      "examples": [
        {
          "chinese": "你是在哪里认识他的？",
          "pinyin": "Nǐ shì zài nǎ lǐ rèn shi tā de?",
          "english": "Where (exactly) did you meet him?"
        },
        {
          "chinese": "他是昨天来的。",
          "pinyin": "Tā shì zuó tiān lái de.",
          "english": "He came yesterday (emphasising when)."
        }
      ],
